snippet.title: Indoor Playground Family Fun Play Area for Kids and Babies Playing, Baby Nursery Rhyme - AmyBabyShow
snippet.description:
This best learning video for kids video from AmyBabyShow is about an indoor playground family fun play area for kids playing and having fun, and baby nursery rhyme songs. Ely and Ela had a family fun playtime at the indoor playground play area for kids while baby Amy and Mom were taking an afternoon nap at home. Fun children playing at the playground. The play area for children had a giant inflatable slide, lots of places for kids jumping, climbing, playing with colored balls and playing with toys. The kids had an awesome fun time playing at the indoor playground that was fun for family and kids. Baby nursery rhyme songs make a fun viewing experience for babies and toddlers.

With a "quack, quack " here and a " quack, quack " there
Here a " quack " there a " quack "
Everywhere a " quack, quack "

Overall tempat di sini jauh lebih gede tapi harga lebih mahal, karena kata petugasnya kalau di sini kan harus nyewa tempat. Karena kalau du AEON Mall, kidzoona jadi part of punya AEON dan dept. storenya. Anyway tetep genji suka dan perosotan dan tempat bikin ice cream masih jadi favoritnya. SERU!

snippet.title: Spell
snippet.description: While flying to his father’s funeral in rural Appalachia, an intense storm causes Marquis (Omari Hardwick) to lose control of the plane carrying him and his family.  He awakens wounded, alone and trapped in Ms. Eloise’s (Loretta Devine) attic, who claims she can nurse him back to health with the Boogity, a Hoodoo figure she has made from his blood and skin. Unable to call for help, Marquis desperately tries to outwit and break free from her dark magic and save his family from a sinister ritual before the rise of the blood moon.

snippet.title: WATERMELON SMASH - Kids Play with Slime? #watermelonsmash || Keith's Toy Box
snippet.description:
YouTube Kids Keith and Bree play Watermelon Smash Game Meme at the swimming pool with water and slime?  Will they get slime or water on their head?
Watermelon Smash is available exclusively at Target.
This is the perfect summer outdoor game with friends and family.
You can also use the plastic seeds for indoor play.

Watermelon Smash was provided free by Yulu toys for review.

#watermelonsmash #yulutoys 

Take a chance on the Watermelon Smash game but don’t be the one to get splashed. This all new hilarious twist on the water roulette game challenges each player to press the watermelon against your head as many times as said on the spinner. A suspenseful game in which you never know when the watermelon will fully crack open. If it cracks on your turn, you either get covered with water or plastic watermelon seeds and you are out of the game.

Be the last player left to avoid having the watermelon crack open and you win. Great for indoor play with seeds or outdoor play with water.

snippet.title: 2020 Montgomery County Sports Hall of Fame Induction Ceremony
snippet.description:
Hello and welcome to the Montgomery County Sports Hall of Fame 2nd Annual Induction Ceremony

Curtis Pride (Baseball), Johnny Holliday (Broadcasting), Amy Wood (Field Hockey), Jeri Ingram (Tennis), Tom Brown (Baseball and Football) and the late Roy Lester (HS Football Coach) are all stellar in their history of representing our community and in their commitments to make Montgomery County a better place.

Curtis Pride's story--born severely hearing impaired, yet excelled in three sports--will bring tears to your eyes. Tom Brown played in the pros in two sports; baseball for the Senators and won three NFL title rings with the Green Bay Packers. Jeri Ingram still holds records in Montgomery County and the University of Maryland. Coaches, like Amy Wood and Roy Lester, are often the unsung heroes behind the stars. But they not only build athletes, they build young men and women who are our county's future. And Johnny Holliday! He is much, much more than the voice of the Terps. Humble and generous of spirit.

Olympic Gold Medalist and 2019 Inductee Dominique Dawes delivers a special message after landing a surprise opening.

Thank you for joining us!

Please visit our website to learn more about this year's inductees, past inductees, and how you can help support the Montgomery County Sports Hall of Fame https://mcshf.org
